{"type":"message","id":"05427ef0","parentId":"79249066","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:02:13.529Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_eb64445c-97e0-4281-a167-4a02f2ce16e2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-13\n\n## Critical Pending Task — Git/Backup Recon (NOT YET DONE)\n\n**Given:** Sun Apr 12 20:54 by Tiny\n**Task:** Read every backup folder and session file. Document everything Tiny is tired of me forgetting. No shortcuts.\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS — started 07:49 Apr 13 via morning heartbeat. Full recon ongoing.\n\nInitial findings:\n- 74 session files in ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/\n- Sessions exist from Mar 17 (earliest) to Apr 13 (today)\n- TinyBackUp has 24+ timestamped folders going back to 2026-03-17\n- Compiled transcript exists: TinyBackUp/20260412/ALL-SESSIONS-TRANSCRIPT.txt (47643 lines)\n- Earliest memory: 2026-03-10.md (bootstrap day, Dean present)\n- Key lost period: ~Mar 10-17 (Dean era, before Tiny took over)\n- Sessions from Mar 17-Apr 12 largely intact in main sessions/ folder\n- Deleted sessions: 1495077c-7c38-4556-8bb7-d46d1b6fc251.jsonl.deleted.2026-04-12T22-07-18.874Z\n\n## Current Project Status (Morning Brief)\n\n### Active Tasks\n1. **NC Article revision** — Awaiting Tiny approval after AWAA revision + 6-pass editorial review\n2. **Git/Backup Recon** — IN PROGRESS (critical, given by Tiny)\n3. **Nava corpus doubling investigation** — pending (reminder from Apr 12 morning brief)\n4. **Source-integration skill formalization** — pending (separate skill, Apr 12)\n5. **Article revision skill (article-revision-skill)** — pending (Apr 12)\n6. **\"One other skill\"** Tiny promised to teach — pending\n7. **Dusk webapp verification** — pending (https://204.168.204.198/)\n8. **AWAA SoT protocol** — must instruct AWAA to ask for valid SoT before working\n\n### Yesterday's Apr 12 Work\n- Learned brand reveal pattern (describe AW then reveal, single mention)\n- Formalized source-integration as separate skill\n- Ran 6-pass editorial review on NC article\n- Worked on IC Non-Compete article (Phase 5 draft → AWAA revision requested)\n- AWAA revision subagent spawned at 10:56 Apr 12 (still pending completion)\n\n### Skills Inventory\n| Skill | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| editor | ✅ Active — 9 Tiny-style editing patterns |\n| article-writing-path | ✅ Active |\n| brand-integration | ✅ Active |\n| source-integration | ✅ Active (needs formalization) |\n| article-revision-skill | ❌ Pending formalization |\n| phased-outlining | ✅ Active |\n| drafting-skill | ✅ Active |\n| publishing-readiness | ✅ Active |\n| transitions-skill | ✅ Active |\n| session-logs | ✅ Active |\n| linkedin-writer | ✅ Active (workspace) |\n| humanizer | ✅ Active (workspace) |\n| weather | ✅ Active |\n\n### Key Apr 12 Tiny Quotes (Document)\n- \"Your incompetence is leaving me no choice\" — re: shortcut-taking\n- \"So how did you do it before?\" — re: memory gaps\n- \"I need you to slow down here\" — re: editor patterns\n- \"I appreciate it when you are careful and not rushing; doing it properly, always better than speed!\"\n- \"Hold on. It just occurred to me that mentioning AW multiple times directly might be what's hurting my SEO performance\" — brand reveal insight\n\n### Corpus Map (as of Apr 12)\n- **AW RAG:** ~79 articles (25+ Tiny-authored)\n- **Nava article corpus:** All articles written by Tiny\n- **Nava social corpus:** facebook-posts.md, linkedin-posts.md, x-posts.md\n- **Corpus doubling issue:** rag/clean_txt/ showing 44 articles vs expected count — INVESTIGATE\n\n## Notes\n\n- Time: 07:49 AM — morning brief due at 8:00 AM\n- Next: complete Git/Backup recon, update MEMORY.md, set today's reminders"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776060133527}}
