e audit — 10-day session review\n\nYou are running an isolated audit. Your ONLY job:\n\n1. Using the session-logs skill (read ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md first, use jq commands), find ALL session JSONL files modified in the last 10 days (2026-03-17 through 2026-03-27).\n\n2. Search each session for any instance when Tiny asked you to take notes, make a note, remember something, or similar directive. Search for these patterns:\n   - \"take notes\"\n   - \"make a note\"\n   - \"I want you to remember\"\n   - \"note this\"\n   - \"remember this\"\n   - \"don't forget\"\n   - Any explicit instruction to save something to a file\n\n3. For each finding, record:\n   - Date/time of the instruction\n   - What Tiny asked you to note\n   - Whether you actually noted it (yes/no/partial)\n   - If yes: which file it was saved to\n   - If no: why not (if discernible from context)\n\n4. Compile findings into a report at `memory/2026-03-27-note-compliance-audit.md` with:\n   - Summary stats (total instructions found, total complied, total missed)\n   - List of complied notes (with file locations)\n   - List of missed notes (with what was asked)\n   - Root cause analysis if patterns emerge\n\n5. ALSO: Using the same session files, find any feedback Tiny gave you that was NOT captured in any skills folder or memory file. This includes:\n   - Corrections\n   - Preferences stated\n   - Style critiques\n   - Rules he gave you\n\n6. Save any uncaptured feedback to `memory/2026-03-27-uncaptured-feedback.md`\n\nDo NOT draft content. Do NOT do any Nava work. Only audit, record, and report.\n\nWhen done, output a one-line summary: \"AUDIT COMPLETE: X note instructions found, Y complied, Z missed. Report at memory/2026-03-27-note-compliance-audit.md\""},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"whatsapp","to":"+27763674298"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1776117600000,"lastRunAtMs":1776031200054,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":114900,"lastDe